# Intuition
Just find right max and left max of a buildng and deduct the building height. Do it for all the buildings and return the sum.

# Approach
For every element calculating the most largest element to its left and right. now the water saved by one building will be min of the left largest and right largest minus the area the covered the that building that is height[i]. Suming it for every building we getting our desired answer.

